<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-249-171 </DOCNO><DOCID>09 846 081</DOCID><JOURNAL>Communications News  Jan 1991 v28 n1 p35(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Credit union switch improves customer service: new phone sets,reports reduce need to spur agents.andM;</TITLE><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Patelco Credit Union comprises 16 branch offices that aresupported by a telephone service center (TSC) which became aseparate department in 1984.andP;  The TSC operates off a TelcomTechnologies ECD-4000EX switching system and Digital Display Sets(DDS) that enable credit union agents to manage calls andtroubleshoot potential system problems.andP;  Ten agents handle some1,200 calls per day, answering questions regarding accounts,balances, check clearances, and savings rates, among other topics.andO;Approximately 48 percent of all calls are handled within fiveseconds; the DDS sets allow agents to identify how many calls arein queue, how long each call takes, and which call has beenwaiting longest.andP;  Additionally, a feature called Enhanced Wrap-Upmakes it possible to keep running tallies of up to 90 differentactivities, reporting the current percentage of both group andsystem totals accounted for by a given activity.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Patelco Credit Union (Communication systems).andO;Product:   Telcom Technologies ECD-4000EX (Telecommunication switchingsystem) (Usage).andO;Topic:     Credit UnionTelecommunication Switching SystemsProductivity.andO;Feature:   illustrationphotograph.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>